data.name: Aspects
desc: The constant set contains possible aspects for an embedded object.

This constant set provides a set of values that can be used to specify the kind of object view. It can be used for example by container to request view representation of a certain kind from XEmbeddedObject.
The first 32 bits are reserved for MS OLE aspects.

items.name: MSOLE_CONTENT
lines: specifies view of the object to be displayed as an embedded object inside a container.

items.name: MSOLE_THUMBNAIL
lines: specifies view of the object to be displayed in a browsing tool.

items.name: MSOLE_ICON
lines: specifies view of the object when object is represented by Icon.

items.name: MSOLE_DOCPRINT
lines: specifies view of the object for print preview.
